   "base_medium": "Shewanella oneidensis MR-1 defined medium (a.k.a. 'MR-1 medium'), lactate as electron donor, PIPES-buffered; modified here to 20 mM sodium lactate",
   "base_medium_reference": "Cited in paper as 'modified MR-1 medium (Cao et al., 2011)'. Two candidate Cao et al. 2011 papers on Shewanella sp. HRCR-1 biofilms from the Beyenal/Fredrickson group: (1) Cao B, et al. 2011, Environ Microbiol 13:1018-1031, DOI 10.1111/j.1462-2920.2010.02407.x, PMID 21251176; (2) Cao B, et al. 2011, Environ Sci Technol 45:5483-5490, DOI 10.1021/es200095j. Both grew HRCR-1/MR-1 in the standard S. oneidensis defined medium whose full composition is documented in the same lineage (e.g. Bretschger et al. 2007, Appl Environ Microbiol, DOI 10.1128/AEM.01087-07). Neither Cao 2011 full text nor the PMC6255981 methods reprint the recipe; composition below is the canonical S. oneidensis MR-1 defined medium repeatedly reported for this organism/group.",
